.TH "srpt_alloc_ioctx_ring" 9 "srpt_alloc_ioctx_ring" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
srpt_alloc_ioctx_ring \- allocate a ring of SRPT I/O context structures
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct srpt_ioctx **" srpt_alloc_ioctx_ring
.BI "(struct srpt_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "int ring_size "  ","
.BI "int ioctx_size "  ","
.BI "struct kmem_cache *buf_cache "  ","
.BI "int alignment_offset "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
Device to allocate the I/O context ring for.
.IP "ring_size" 12
Number of elements in the I/O context ring.
.IP "ioctx_size" 12
I/O context size.
.IP "buf_cache" 12
I/O buffer cache.
.IP "alignment_offset" 12
Offset in each ring buffer at which the SRP information
unit starts.
.IP "dir" 12
DMA data direction.
